# Admonitions
Use admonitions to highlight important information. Syntax:
```
\`\`\`ad-<type>
Content goes here
\`\`\`
```

Available types and when to use them:
- `ad-note` - General notes, neutral information
- `ad-abstract`/`ad-summary`/`ad-tldr` - Key takeaways, summaries
- `ad-info` - Supplementary information, context
- `ad-tip`/`ad-hint`/`ad-important` - Helpful advice, best practices
- `ad-success`/`ad-check`/`ad-done` - Successful outcomes, completed items
- `ad-question`/`ad-help`/`ad-faq` - Questions to consider, help needed
- `ad-warning`/`ad-caution`/`ad-attention` - Important warnings, gotchas
- `ad-failure`/`ad-fail`/`ad-missing` - Common mistakes, failure cases
- `ad-danger`/`ad-error` - Critical issues, errors to avoid
- `ad-bug` - Known bugs or issues
- `ad-example` - Code examples, use cases
- `ad-quote`/`ad-cite` - Quotations, citations

Guidelines:
- Use sparingly (1-3 per note max) to maintain focus
- Place at natural breaks in content flow
